#filtering top3 intersections
top_3 = top_intersections_3.nlargest(3).index
grouped_data_top3 = peak_junctions[peak_junctions['Area Name'].isin(top_3)]


plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.barplot(x='Area Name', y='Traffic Volume', hue='Intersection_name', data=grouped_data_top3, palette='Set2',ci=None)
plt.title('Mean Traffic Volume for Top 3 Areas by Traffic Volume')
plt.xlabel('Area Name', labelpad=14)
plt.ylabel('Mean Traffic Volume')
plt.grid(True, which='both', axis='y', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.7)
plt.xticks(rotation=0, ha='center')
plt.legend(title='Intersection Name', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
